"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926440","Home Office","false","2018-06-28","<p>We are committed to giving the police the necessary tools to do their job and TASER®, a form of conducted energy device (CED), provides officers with an important less-lethal, tactical option when facing potentially physically violent situations</p><p>While its use must be in line with the Home Secretary’s authorisation of the device, the deployment of TASER® is an operational matter for Chief Officers. It is for them to determine the number of devices and specially trained officers based on their force assessment of threat and risk</p><p>The use of CEDs is currently limited to officers who have completed their probationary period and been confirmed in rank. Officers who wish to undertake CED training are also required to have the support of their supervisor and have to successfully pass the training. Any change to this model, including the eligibility of officers to apply for special training, would require formal consideration by the Home Secretary.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2018-06-28T13:51:01.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926440/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926440/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926440/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-18","Police: Stun Guns","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether any category of police officer dealing with the public is excluded from being eligible for training in the use of Tasers and from being issued with them; and if so, on what grounds.","false","Biography information for Lord Davies of Stamford",,"Lord Davies of Stamford","HL8701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926441","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-24","<p>The United Kingdom adheres to the World Health Organization Global Code of Practice on the International Recruitment of Health Personnel. The UK Government has developed a list of developing countries, based on economic status and the availability of healthcare professionals that should not be targeted for recruitment without Government-to-Government agreement.</p><p>The list is based upon the Organisation for Economic Cooperation and Development’s Development Assistance Committee list of aid recipients and can be found in the attached table, due to the size of the data.</p><p>There are three important exceptions to this list. First, there is Memorandum of Understanding between the UK and Philippine Governments to enable the UK to recruit registered nurses and other healthcare professionals that are regulated by appropriate professional bodies in both countries. Second, the inclusion of India on this list is in relation to four states: Andhra Pradesh, Madhya Pradesh, Orissa and West Bengal. These states currently receive assistance from the Department for International Development. Finally, the Chinese Government has requested that China is removed from this list but that no recruitment should take place in small rural areas.</p><p>Specific agreements also exist for exchange programmes, or medical training initiatives, which enable health care professionals to come to the UK on a temporary basis to learn new skills before returning to their home country. For example, the Government announced such a scheme in partnership with the Jamaican Government in April this year.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2018-07-24T15:42:57.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926441/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926441/answer","List of developing countries that should not be targeted for recruitment of health service personnel.docx","List of developing countries that should not be targeted for recruitment of health service personnel.docx","Countries which should not be targeted","Countries which should not be targeted","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926441/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-18","NHS: Migrant Workers","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the answer by the Earl of Courtown on 12 June (HL Deb, col 1575), from which countries it would not be acceptable for the NHS to recruit nurses and doctors.","false","Biography information for Lord Davies of Stamford",,"Lord Davies of Stamford","HL8702"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926442","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-28","<p>We recognise that information and data sharing is essential to delivering high quality, integrated health and social care and this Government is committed to ensuring that data sharing is done safely, securely and legally.</p><p>There are currently no plans to allow the Summary Care Record to be accessed by English hospitals for patients who are registered with general practitioner surgeries in Scotland.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2018-06-28T16:25:49.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926442/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926442/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926442/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-18","Out of Area Treatment","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether, in the context of unplanned admissions to hospitals by patients registered in Scotland, English hospitals are able to access an individuals patient's records for the purpose of admission and medical history; and if not, whether they propose to enable such arrangements.","false","Biography information for Lord Glenarthur",,"Lord Glenarthur","HL8703"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926444","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-06-27","<p>The Department reviews generation performance of a range of existing and new renewables plants, including onshore and offshore wind, on an annual basis as part of setting the level of the Renewables Obligation. The most recent publication can be found here (copy also attached):</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/renewables-obligation-level-calculations-201819" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/renewables-obligation-level-calculations-201819</a></p><p> </p><p>The Department periodically reviews the evidence base on the generation costs of renewable electricity technologies, including their lifetimes, and when appropriate publishes reports on the topic. The most recent of these publications can be found here and attached (copy also attached):</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/beis-electricity-generation-costs-november-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/beis-electricity-generation-costs-november-2016</a></p><p> </p>",,"Lord Henley",,"2018-06-27T16:36:22.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926444/answer","Biography information for Lord Henley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926444/answer","Renewables_Obligation_2018_19_FINAL.pdf ; BEIS_Electricity_Generation_Cost_Report.pdf","Renewables_Obligation_2018_19_FINAL.pdf ; BEIS_Electricity_Generation_Cost_Report.pdf","The Renewables Obligation For 2018/19 ; Electricity Generation Costs","The Renewables Obligation For 2018/19 ; Electricity Generation Costs","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926444/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-06-18","Wind Power","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what measures they are taking to monitor any change in performance of wind turbines in on-shore and off-shore locations from their time of construction; whether they intend to publish assessments of the likely future lifetime of the wind turbine systems now being constructed in the UK; and if so, whether this information will be provided to organisations that are investing in such systems.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Chesterton",,"Lord Hunt of Chesterton","HL8704"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926446","Department for Education","false","2018-07-02","<p>The Department for Education recently conducted a thorough engagement process on the scope and content of relationships education and relationships and sex education, and on the status of personal, social, health and economic education. This involved a wide range of interested stakeholders and a public call for evidence, which generated over 23,000 responses.</p><p>We plan to publish the results of the call for evidence shortly alongside a consultation on draft regulations and associated guidance, before laying the regulations in the House for debate. Following approval of the regulations, schools will be able to make use of the statutory guidance to begin delivery of the new subjects.</p><p>We are using the evidence gathered from the engagement exercises to determine what resources, training or additional support should be available to teachers in delivering high quality teaching in this area of the curriculum. We will continue to consult on this important issue alongside the draft regulations and guidance.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Agnew of Oulton","HL8706","2018-07-02T15:48:07.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926446/answer","Biography information for Lord Agnew of Oulton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926446/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926446/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-06-18","Sex and Relationship Education","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government when they plan to publish the revised curriculum and draft regulations to introduce statutory relationship education at primary level and sex and relationship education at secondary level into the new curriculum in September.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL8705"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926447","Department for Education","false","2018-07-02","<p>The Department for Education recently conducted a thorough engagement process on the scope and content of relationships education and relationships and sex education, and on the status of personal, social, health and economic education. This involved a wide range of interested stakeholders and a public call for evidence, which generated over 23,000 responses.</p><p>We plan to publish the results of the call for evidence shortly alongside a consultation on draft regulations and associated guidance, before laying the regulations in the House for debate. Following approval of the regulations, schools will be able to make use of the statutory guidance to begin delivery of the new subjects.</p><p>We are using the evidence gathered from the engagement exercises to determine what resources, training or additional support should be available to teachers in delivering high quality teaching in this area of the curriculum. We will continue to consult on this important issue alongside the draft regulations and guidance.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Agnew of Oulton","HL8705","2018-07-02T15:48:07.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926447/answer","Biography information for Lord Agnew of Oulton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926447/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926447/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-06-18","Teachers: Training","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of the time needed for training teachers to deliver effectively the new curriculum due to be introduced in September.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL8706"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926448","Department for International Development","false","2018-06-28","<p>Through the United Nations Relief and Works Agency (UNRWA) Syria Emergency Appeal, the UK continues to support Palestinian refugees in Syria, including those who are displaced following the siege of Yarmouk. The UK remains in dialogue with UNRWA as they assess and develop contingency plans to assist displaced Palestinian refugees, including should they be evicted from Yarmouk, Yalda, Babbila and Beit Sahem.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2018-06-28T16:26:24.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926448/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926448/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926448/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-06-18","Palestinians: Syria","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether they will consult the United Nations Relief and Works Agency for Palestine Refugees in the Near East and other UN agencies about what can be done for the Palestinians formerly living in Yarmouk, who moved to Babbila, Yalda and Beit Sahem but who now face eviction.","false","Biography information for Lord Hylton",,"Lord Hylton","HL8707"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926449","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-29","<p>The UK strongly supports the work of the OSCE election observation mission to monitor the campaign environment and conduct of the Turkish elections, including any accusations of violence linked to the campaign. We have contributed observers to the mission. We make it clear that elections had to take place in a peaceful atmosphere and needed to respect for international standards and fundamental freedoms.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2018-06-29T12:14:02.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926449/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926449/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926449/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-18","Turkey: Elections","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether they will report to the OSCE monitors the recent detentions and arrests of HDP officials and attacks on their offices in Ankara and Hatay.","false","Biography information for Lord Hylton",,"Lord Hylton","HL8708"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926451","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-27","<p>​We have been closely following Turkey’s Operation Tigris Shield, announced in March in order to combat Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) fighters in the Turkey-Iraq border regions. The PKK remains a significant threat to Turkey and is an internationally proscribed terrorist organisation. We have not discussed the current operation in international fora, but will continue to engage with the Turkish Government on their operations as appropriate.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2018-06-27T12:32:24.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926451/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926451/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926451/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-18","Iraq: Military Intervention","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what information they have about Turkish military actions (1) inside Iraq under Operation Tigris Shield, and (2) in Duhok and Erbil provinces, and plans to attack the Candil Mountains; and whether such actions have been discussed in any international forum.","false","Biography information for Lord Hylton",,"Lord Hylton","HL8709"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926452","Department for International Development","false","2018-06-27","<p>The Rupert’s Wharf is in use and the Government of St Helena is developing a business case to expand its operations. This will include options for funding and timescales for completion.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2018-06-27T16:18:29.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926452/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926452/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926452/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-06-18","St Helena: Ports","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government when the new wharf at Rupert’s Bay, St Helena, will be fully operational.","false","Biography information for Lord Jones of Cheltenham",,"Lord Jones of Cheltenham","HL8710"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926453","Department for International Development","false","2018-06-27","<p>The Rupert’s Wharf is in use and the Government of St Helena is developing a business case to expand its operations. This will include options for funding and timescales for completion.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2018-06-27T16:32:59.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926453/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926453/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926453/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-06-18","St Helena: Ports","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what is the reason for the delay between the completion of the construction of the new wharf at Rupert’s Bay, St Helena, and the commencement of the construction of the supporting infrastructure such as container lay-down areas.","false","Biography information for Lord Jones of Cheltenham",,"Lord Jones of Cheltenham","HL8711"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926454","Department for International Development","false","2018-06-27","<p>The Government of St Helena is developing a business case for the supporting infrastructure at Rupert’s Bay. The detailed design work will be the next step in the process and will determine the design life among other value for money choices.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2018-06-27T16:33:08.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926454/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926454/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926454/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-06-18","St Helena: Ports","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what the design life will be for the supporting infrastructure at Rupert’s Bay, St Helena, including container lay-down areas.","false","Biography information for Lord Jones of Cheltenham",,"Lord Jones of Cheltenham","HL8712"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926455","Department for International Development","false","2018-06-27","<p>The costs of transferring freight from Rupert’s Wharf to James Bay are included in the St Helena Government’s draft budget for 2018/19, which is yet to be agreed by St Helena’s Elected Members. Through our programme of financial aid, DFID will contribute the majority of funds to that budget. Since the new air service and associated sea freight arrangements have been put in place, the cost to the St Helena and UK taxpayers are significantly less than under the previous arrangements.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2018-06-27T16:34:21.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926455/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926455/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926455/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-06-18","St Helena: Ports","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of the additional cost in terms of both time and money of off-loading ships’ cargo at St Helena in cases where it is necessary for the cargo to be off-loaded at the new wharf at Rupert’s Bay and then ferried by barge to the old wharf at James’s Bay due to the absence of supporting infrastructure such as container lay-down areas at Rupert’s Bay.","false","Biography information for Lord Jones of Cheltenham",,"Lord Jones of Cheltenham","HL8713"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926457","Department for International Development","false","2018-06-27","<p>We are confident that air services to St Helena will not be affected in the short term as Basil Read Ltd pursues a business rescue process. Alongside the St Helena Government, we will ensure alternative plans are available to continue airport operations in the event that they become necessary.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2018-06-27T16:34:33.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926457/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926457/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926457/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-06-18","St Helena: Airports","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of the possible impact on the running of the airport on St Helena of the current operators of the airport, Basil Read, voluntarily entering a Business Rescue process; and what contingency plans they are developing to maintain operation of the airport.","false","Biography information for Lord Jones of Cheltenham",,"Lord Jones of Cheltenham","HL8714"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926458","Department for International Development","false","2018-06-27","<p>Twice weekly commercial flights to St Helena for the 2018/19 peak visitor season are scheduled to commence on Tuesday 4 December 2018.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2018-06-27T16:36:37.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926458/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926458/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926458/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-06-18","St Helena: Aviation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government when they expect the second flight each week to St Helena to commence.","false","Biography information for Lord Jones of Cheltenham",,"Lord Jones of Cheltenham","HL8715"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926459","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-07-02","<p>On 18 June my Department published a consultation on banning the use of combustible materials in the external walls of high-rise residential buildings. This is available (attached) at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/banning-the-use-of-combustible-materials-in-the-external-walls-of-high-rise-residential-buildings" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/banning-the-use-of-combustible-materials-in-the-external-walls-of-high-rise-residential-buildings</a></p><p>As a Devolved Administration the decisions of the Welsh Assembly Government are an issue devolved for their own consideration.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2018-07-02T16:29:04.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926459/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926459/answer","180621 Combustible Cladding Consultation - HL8716.pdf","180621 Combustible Cladding Consultation - HL8716.pdf","Consultation document","Consultation document","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926459/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-06-18","High Rise Flats: Insulation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of the decision of the Welsh Government to ban the use of combustible cladding on high rise residential buildings.","false","Biography information for Lord Kennedy of Southwark",,"Lord Kennedy of Southwark","HL8716"
