"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926577","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-21","<p>The information requested is not collected centrally and could not be obtained without incurring disproportionate cost.</p><p>Good education in and out of the classroom and purposeful activity are the key to unlocking a secure and stable future for young people and I am determined to drive forward our comprehensive reforms so that young people are equipped with the skills to live successful, crime-free lives on release.</p>","Charnwood","Edward Argar",,"2018-06-21T09:03:48.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926577/answer","Biography information for Edward Argar","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926577/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926577/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-06-18","Young Offender Institutions: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the average number of hours per week  was of taught education and vocational training provided to children held in a segregation block in each Young Offender Institution in each month in 2018.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","154763"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926578","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-26","<p>Whilst we have not raised the case of Laith Abu Zeyad, our Consul General in Jerusalem raised our concerns over the actions of the Palestinian Authority (PA) security forces and police during the demonstration held in Ramallah on 13 June. He stressed the need for an investigation to understand what happened, to learn the lessons and to enable appropriate action to be taken.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-06-26T17:01:57.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926578/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926578/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926578/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-18","Laith Abu Zeyad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has made representations to his Palestinian counterparts on the case of Amnesty International staff member, Laith Abu Zeyad; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","154673"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926579","Treasury","false","2018-06-26","<p>This level of detail is not requested on VAT returns and therefore we do not have data available on how much VAT revenue was accrued or refunded in relation to particular products.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","154784","2018-06-26T09:17:59.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926579/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926579/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926579/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-18","Medical Equipment: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the VAT revenue accrued to the public purse from the procurement of (a) medical equipment, (b) lifesaving emergency equipment and (c) defibrillators in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","154783"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926580","Treasury","false","2018-06-26","<p>This level of detail is not requested on VAT returns and therefore we do not have data available on how much VAT revenue was accrued or refunded in relation to particular products.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","154783","2018-06-26T09:17:59.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926580/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926580/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926580/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-18","Medical Equipment: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the VAT refunds made in relation to the procurement of (a) medical equipment, (b) lifesaving medical emergency medical equipment and (c) defibrillators, in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","154784"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926581","Treasury","false","2018-06-26","<p>We recognise that provision of defibrillators could help those who have a cardiac arrest outside a hospital setting. The government maintains several VAT reliefs to aid purchases of defibrillators, including purchases made by local authorities and those made through voluntary contributions which are donated to eligible charities or the NHS.</p><p> </p><p>The current framework of European law limits further VAT reliefs being applied to defibrillators. Our future relationship with the EU, including on VAT, is subject to negotiation. Any future decisions on VAT will continue to be taken in line with the normal Budget process.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-06-26T09:13:03.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926581/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926581/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926581/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-18","Medical Equipment: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he has plans to review the policy of charging VAT on (a) defibrillators and (b) other medical equipment.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","154785"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926582","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-06-27","<p>Fuel poverty is a devolved issue, each nation in the UK has its own fuel poverty definition, targets and policies to tackle the issue.</p><p>In 2015, the proportion of fuel poor households in England with no connection to the gas grid was estimated to be 18.5% (463,000 households).</p><p>The proportion of fuel poor households in England with at least one prepayment meter was estimated to be 32.9% (823,000 households).</p><p>The proportion of fuel poor households in England using electric central heating was 8.2% (204,000 households).</p><p>The latest fuel poverty detailed tables for England can be found at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/fuel-poverty-detailed-tables-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/fuel-poverty-detailed-tables-2017</a></p><p>Note that the latest fuel poverty annual statistics for England are due to be published on the 26<sup>th</sup> of June, 2018.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-06-27T15:53:04.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926582/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926582/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926582/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-06-18","Fuel Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what proportion of households in fuel poverty have (a) no connection to the gas grid, (b) at least one prepayment meter installed and (c) electric central heating.","false","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael","154614"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926583","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-06-27","<p>Fuel poverty is a devolved matter, each nation in the UK has its own fuel poverty definition, targets and policies to tackle the issue.</p><p> </p><p>Between 2010 and 2015, the number of households in fuel poverty in England was estimated to be as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>SAP bands</strong></p></td><td colspan="6"><p><strong>Number of households (thousands)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>2015</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>A/B/C</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>68</p></td><td><p>104</p></td><td><p>104</p></td><td><p>135</p></td><td><p>151</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>D</p></td><td><p>694</p></td><td><p>772</p></td><td><p>893</p></td><td><p>1055</p></td><td><p>1199</p></td><td><p>1337</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>E</p></td><td><p>1227</p></td><td><p>1146</p></td><td><p>1015</p></td><td><p>875</p></td><td><p>758</p></td><td><p>736</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>F and G</p></td><td><p>531</p></td><td><p>447</p></td><td><p>348</p></td><td><p>313</p></td><td><p>287</p></td><td><p>278</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>* Figures have been suppressed due to small sample size</p><p> </p><p><em>Source: BEIS data <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/fuel-poverty-trends-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/fuel-poverty-trends-2017</a></em></p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-06-27T15:53:47.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926583/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926583/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926583/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-06-18","Fuel Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many households in fuel poverty have a home that is rated (a) band C, (b) band D, (c) band E and (d) lower than band E for energy efficiency.","false","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael","154615"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926584","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-06-27","<p>The Department does not hold the number of households in fuel poverty that have had their homes upgraded since January 2015.</p><p>Due to the nature of the survey, on which the fuel poverty statistics are based, the department cannot track when an energy efficiency measure is installed in a property and the resulting change in efficiency rating.</p><p>The fuel poverty trends tables estimate the number of households in each energy efficiency band between 2003 and 2015, these tables can be found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/fuel-poverty-trends-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/fuel-poverty-trends-2017</a>.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-06-27T15:56:02.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926584/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926584/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926584/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-06-18","Fuel Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many households in fuel poverty have had their homes upgraded since January 2015 to band (a) C, (b) D and (c) E for energy efficiency.","false","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael","154616"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926585","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-06-27","<p>According to Ofgem statistics, between 1 April 2014 and 31 March 2017, the Gas Distribution Networks in Great Britain made 37,597 connections under the Fuel Poor Network Extension Scheme.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-06-27T15:57:23.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926585/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926585/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926585/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-06-18","Fuel Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many households have been connected to the gas grid under the fuel poor network extension scheme since 1 April 2014.","false","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael","154617"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926586","Home Office","false","2018-06-21","<p>As per the answer on 12 June (UIN 151250 and 151251 refer), the Government does not require specific DNA evidence to be provided in immigration cases.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","154814","2018-06-21T16:55:47.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926586/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926586/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926586/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-18","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the answer of 12 June 2018 to Question 151251 on Immigration, in how many cases his Department has asked an applicant for a visa or asylum to provide DNA tests to prove that British-born children are their own in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Afzal Khan","Manchester, Gorton","Afzal Khan","154813"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926587","Home Office","false","2018-06-21","<p>As per the answer on 12 June (UIN 151250 and 151251 refer), the Government does not require specific DNA evidence to be provided in immigration cases.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","154813","2018-06-21T16:55:47.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926587/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926587/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926587/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-18","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 12 June to Question 151250 on Immigration, whether it is his Department's policy to request applicants for (a) visas and (b) asylum to provide DNA tests to prove British-born children are theirs.","false","Biography information for Afzal Khan","Manchester, Gorton","Afzal Khan","154814"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926588","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-21","<p>The Prime Minister has announced a five-year funding agreement which will see the National Health Service budget grow by £20 billion by 2023/24. The Government will work with the NHS to develop a ten-year plan setting out how the money will be used for the future of the health service across policy areas, which will then inform local allocations including for Devon, Cornwall and Plymouth.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-06-21T11:21:02.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926588/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926588/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926588/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-18","NHS: South West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what proportion of the additional spending that will be allocated to the NHS will be allocated to health services in (a) Devon, (b) Cornwall and (c) Plymouth.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","154815"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926589","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-21","<p>We are considering the impact of the Agenda for Change multi-year pay deal on those organisations who are not listed in Annex 1 to the National Health Service Terms and Conditions of Service Handbook, including social enterprises providing NHS services, and will be confirming the position shortly.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-06-21T11:16:13.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926589/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926589/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926589/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-18","NHS: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether he plans to extend the NHS pay settlement to staff of social enterprises.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","154816"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926590","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-06-26","<p>The intent is to store the remaining three Trafalgar Class submarines, when they are decommissioned, at Her Majesty's Naval Base Devonport prior to dismantling under the Submarine Dismantling Project.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-06-26T15:00:04.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926590/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926590/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926590/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-06-18","Trafalgar Class Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what storage locations have been identified for the three Trafalgar class submarines when they come out of service.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","154817"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926591","Cabinet Office","false","2018-06-21","<p>All those who hold public office are expected to maintain high standards of behaviour and uphold the highest standards of propriety. The Government is confident that the relevant Codes of Conduct for Ministers, Special Advisers and Civil Servants clearly set out the standards of behaviour expected of them in their roles.</p><p> </p><p>Furthermore, all public office holders are expected to observe the Seven Principles of Public Life which are included within these codes.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2018-06-21T09:30:02.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926591/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926591/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926591/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-06-18","Public Service: Conduct","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what assessment he has made of the efficacy of systems to maintain ethical standards for people who hold public office.","false","Biography information for Rosie Cooper","West Lancashire","Rosie Cooper","154641"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926592","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-21","<p>Serving and former armed forces personnel and their families access a wide range of services provided by the National Health Service in England, including mental health services. These are not identified separately in clinical commissioning groups’ accounts.</p><p> </p><p>In addition to this, NHS England was allocated £6.4 million in 2017/18 for bespoke veterans’ mental health services including the Veterans Mental Health Transition, Intervention and Liaison service and the Post Traumatic Stress Disorder service.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","154718","2018-06-21T11:27:51.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926592/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926592/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926592/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-18","Mental Health Services: Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how much funding his Department allocated to mental health services for armed forces personnel in 2017-18.","true","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","154717"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926593","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-21","<p>Operators taking part in the trial signed an undertaking stating that the raw data is to be submitted to Risk Solutions, the independent company managing the trial evaluation, rather than to the Department for Transport (DfT). Information can also be submitted to Risk Solutions by operators marked commercially confidential.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Transport and Risk Solutions have further agreed that the data files will be held on secure systems by Risk Solutions; will not be shared with DfT and will only be used solely for analysis in connection with this trial; will only appear in analysis in a form that does not allow identification of individual companies; and will be securely deleted at the end of the trial. This agreement has been published as a commitment to all operators.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-06-21T10:25:04.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926593/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926593/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926593/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-18","Trailers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department has signed confidentiality agreements with businesses involved in the trials of longer semi-trailers; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","154725"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926594","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-21","<p>The effect on other road users is being assessed in two ways, recording both safety and emissions/congestion.</p><p>All safety incidents on the public highway (also including at service areas, car parks etc.) are reportable under the terms of the trial. The injury incident rates (per km) for longer semi-trailers compared to other articulated HGVs were noted in the 2016 Annual Report. The longer semi-trailers on the trial are being operated more safely than the trailers they replace both nationally and on roads in urban areas, with the injury incident rate being around 30% of the rate for all articulated HGVs.</p><p>The reduction in the number of trips required to deliver the same goods also benefits other road users in terms of reduced injury risk exposure, as well as emissions/pollution and congestion. Where longer semi-trailers are used, the 2016 Annual Report showed an average saving of one in 20 journeys (5%) across all operators rising to one in 9 ((11.5%) for those operators consistently using the trailers at maximum loading.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-06-21T10:21:44.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926594/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926594/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926594/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-18","Trailers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to his Department's trial of longer semi-trailers of travel on (a) urban and (b) minor roads, what assessment he has made of the effect of those trailers on other road users.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","154726"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926595","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-21","<p>The 2016 Longer Semi-trailer mileage figures can be found on page 19 of the 2016 Annual Report which is available online. The trailers are not all fitted with GPS so estimates of urban/rural or other location information is being generated using route modelling based on the start and end postcodes of each journey. The initial modelling of 2016 data, for which both start and end postcodes were available, produced an average figures of 8% Urban (defined as Urban and Non-Motorway).</p><p>The 2017 annual report will be published in September 2018. It will contain 2017 data, including a breakdown by both urban/rural (based on ONS areas) and by road type (Trunk/Principal/Minor). The data has not been broken down by nation.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-06-21T10:19:01.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926595/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926595/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926595/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-18","Trailers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the mileage driven on (a) urban and (b) rural minor roads in (i) England, (ii) Scotland and (iii) Wales was of longer semi-trailers in his Department's trials in 2016 and 2017.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","154727"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926596","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-21","<p>Serving and former armed forces personnel and their families access a wide range of services provided by the National Health Service in England, including mental health services. These are not identified separately in clinical commissioning groups’ accounts.</p><p> </p><p>In addition to this, NHS England was allocated £6.4 million in 2017/18 for bespoke veterans’ mental health services including the Veterans Mental Health Transition, Intervention and Liaison service and the Post Traumatic Stress Disorder service.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","154717","2018-06-21T11:27:51.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926596/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926596/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926596/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-18","Mental Health Services: Veterans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how much funding his Department allocated to mental health services for people who are retired from the armed forces in 2017-18.","true","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","154718"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926597","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-21","<p>Social isolation and loneliness are different concepts but have very close links. Given also the close links between them and poor physical and mental health, I am a member of the newly formed Ministerial Group on Loneliness.</p><p> </p><p>To support the Government’s commitment to tackling loneliness, including a new loneliness strategy and fund, the Department will continue to support policies and programmes such as social prescribing, dementia friendly communities, improved mental health and the recently published Carers Action Plan.</p><p> </p><p>Feelings of social isolation and loneliness are not exclusive to the elderly but this group can be particularly affected. The Green Paper on the care of older people which will be published in the autumn, will set out a number of proposals to help older people live healthier, longer, and more independent lives.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-06-21T16:56:19.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926597/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926597/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926597/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-18","Loneliness: Older People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps his Department is taking to reduce social isolation among the elderly.","true","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","154719"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926598","Cabinet Office","false","2018-06-21","<p>Departments are required to publish each month their total workforce costs on gov.uk.</p><p> </p><p>These are available on GOV.UK <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/policies/government-transparency-and-accountability?keywords=workforce+management+information&amp;public_timestamp%5Bfrom%5D=&amp;public_timestamp%5Bto%5D=" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/policies/government-transparency-and-accountability?keywords=workforce+management+information&amp;public_timestamp%5Bfrom%5D=&amp;public_timestamp%5Bto%5D=</a></p><p> </p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-06-21T11:59:50.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926598/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926598/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926598/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-06-18","Civil Servants: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how much money from the public purse was disbursed in civil service pay by all Departments in April 2018.","false","Biography information for Tommy Sheppard","Edinburgh East","Tommy Sheppard","154749"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926599","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-21","<p>I refer the honourable Member for Leeds East to the answer I gave to PQ 147778 and 147779 on 4<sup>th</sup> June 2018 which sets out full details of recent Family Justice Board meetings.</p><p>The Family Justice Council has met four times a year in 2012, 2013, 2014, 2015, 2016 and 2017, and it has met twice so far in 2018 by the date of this answer.</p><p>The Performance Improvement Sub Group has met four times a year in 2012, 2013, 2014, 2015, 2016 and 2017, and has met on one occasion this year by the date of this answer with the next meeting scheduled in July.</p><p>The Family Justice Young People’s Board has met four times a year in 2013, 2014, five times in 2015, four times in 2016 and 2017, and twice so far in 2018 by the date of this answer. My department has no data for meetings in 2012.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer","154765","2018-06-21T16:12:12.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926599/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926599/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926599/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-06-18","Family Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, on how many occasions the Family Justice (a) Council, (b) Young People’s Board and (c) Performance Improvement sub-group has met in each year since 2012.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","154764"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926600","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-21","<p>I refer the honourable Member for Leeds East to the answer I gave to PQ 147778 and 147779 on 4<sup>th</sup> June 2018 which sets out full details of recent Family Justice Board meetings.</p><p>The Family Justice Council has met four times a year in 2012, 2013, 2014, 2015, 2016 and 2017, and it has met twice so far in 2018 by the date of this answer.</p><p>The Performance Improvement Sub Group has met four times a year in 2012, 2013, 2014, 2015, 2016 and 2017, and has met on one occasion this year by the date of this answer with the next meeting scheduled in July.</p><p>The Family Justice Young People’s Board has met four times a year in 2013, 2014, five times in 2015, four times in 2016 and 2017, and twice so far in 2018 by the date of this answer. My department has no data for meetings in 2012.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer","154764","2018-06-21T16:12:12.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926600/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926600/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926600/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-06-18","Family Justice Board","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, on how many occasions the Family Justice Board has met in each year since 2012.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","154765"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926601","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-21","<p>The total value of contracts that the Ministry of Justice has with Serco, including Private Finance Initiative prison contracts is £3.6bn.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-06-21T16:19:46.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926601/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926601/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926601/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-06-18","Ministry of Justice: Serco","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the total value is of contracts between his Department and Serco.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","154766"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926602","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-26","<p>The Ministry of Justice has direct contracts with Serco and in the case of the Private Finance Prisons(PFIs) that Serco are the custodial service provider, the Ministry of Justice has a contractual relationship with the relevant Special Purpose Vehicles (SPV).</p><p> </p><p>In our contracts directly with Serco the Ministry of Justice pays Serco directly and in the case of PFI prisons, the Ministry of Justice pays the relevant SPV who will then pay Serco as the operating subcontractor. A break-down of spend is as follows:</p><p> </p><p><em>Table 1 – All Serco Contracts including PFIs</em></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Supplier</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010/11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011/12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012/13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013/14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014/15</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015/16</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016/17</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2017/18</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2018/19</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>SERCO GROUP PLC</strong></p></td><td><p>£250.8</p></td><td><p>£236.2m</p></td><td><p>£264.8m</p></td><td><p>£233.6m</p></td><td><p>£255.1m</p></td><td><p>£200.3m</p></td><td><p>£200.1m</p></td><td><p>£202.2m</p></td><td><p>£39.6m</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><em>Table 2 - Serco Contract Spend Excluding PFIs</em></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Supplier</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010/11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011/12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012/13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013/14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014/15</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015/16</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016/17</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2017/18</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2018/19</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>SERCO </strong></p></td><td><p>£140m</p></td><td><p>£144.1m</p></td><td><p>£137.4m</p></