"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926663","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-06-21","<p>The Department receives representations from local authorities on a range of matters relating to funding, although I am not aware of any relating specifically to rodent infestations. Over this spending period the Government has made available over £200 billion for councils to spend on locally determined priorities including public health matters.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak","154807","2018-06-21T16:05:08.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926663/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926663/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926663/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-06-18","Rodents: Urban Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what representations his Department has received from local authorities on (a) rodent and (b) rat infestations in urban areas in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Dan Carden","Liverpool, Walton","Dan Carden","154806"
