or example the Department of Health and Social Care is currently working with Carers Trust on a project to support the effective identification and engagement of young carers.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","154730","2018-06-21T16:29:40.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926714/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926714/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926714/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-06-18","Carers: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what plans he has to ensure that children who provide care to a family member receive adequate support.","false","Biography information for Judith Cummins","Bradford South","Judith Cummins","154731"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926715","Home Office","false","2018-06-21","<p>Information on processing of settlement visas against performance standards is published in the Migration Transparency data at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/international-operations-transparency-data-may-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/international-operations-transparency-data-may-2018</a></p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-21T13:57:37.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926715/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926715/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926715/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-18","Visas: Married People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many applications have been made for spouse visas through the priority settlement programme; and how many of those applications were processed within 30 days.","false","Biography information for Judith Cummins","Bradford South","Judith Cummins","154732"
